msgid "Participation in the project group"
msgstr ""

#: src/2835-project-safe-transmute.md:72
msgid ""
"Like any Rust group, the safe transmute project group intends to operate in "
"a public and open fashion and welcomes participation. Visit the [repository]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang/project-safe-transmute) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: src/2835-project-safe-transmute.md:76
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/2835-project-safe-transmute.md:79
msgid ""
"It is possible that the scope of this endeavor is not large enough to "
"warrant a separate project group."
msgstr ""

#: src/2835-project-safe-transmute.md:81
msgid ""
"It can be argued that the design space has not been fully explored as "
"evidenced by the many crates that address the issue without one being the "
"clear \"go to\", and thus this issue should be left to libraries for further "
"iteration. We believe that while there is no clear winner among existing "
"crates, they are stable enough, small enough and share enough implementation "
"characteristics to be ready for the community to rally around one design "
"direction in the standard library."
msgstr ""

